The '''KN-3 reactor''' (VM-16) is the [[nuclear reactor]] used in pairs to power the [[Kirov class battlecruiser|''Kirov''-class battlecruisers]]. The reactor was also intended to be used on the [[Soviet aircraft carrier Ulyanovsk|''Ulyanovsk'' class]] of [[supercarrier]]s. It is a [[pressurized water reactor]] (PWR), using [[enriched uranium|enriched]] [[uranium-235]] fuel to produce [[megawatt|300 MW]] of power.

It was developed by [[OKBM Afrikantov]].

