{{Infobox Protected area | name = Minsontaung Wildlife Sanctuary | iucn_category = IV | photo = | photo_caption = | map = Myanmar | relief = 1 | map_alt = | map_caption = Location within Burma | map_width = | location =[[Myingyan District]], [[Mandalay Division]], [[Burma]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coord|21|25|46|N|95|47|38|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | area = {{convert|22.6|km2|sqmi|sigfig=2}} | established = 1998-99 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }} '''Minsontaung Wildlife Sanctuary''' or '''Minzontaung Wildlife Sanctuary''' is a [[protected area]] of [[Burma]]. It is located in the [[Natogyi Township]] area, [[Myingyan District]], [[Mandalay Division]]. It occupies an area of {{convert|22.6|km2|sqmi|sigfig=2}} and was established in 1998-99.<ref>[http://www.protectedplanet.net/sites/Minsontaung_Wildlife_Sanctuary Protected Planet - Minsontaung Wildlife Sanctuary]</ref> ==Flora and fauna== The dominant flora is [[dry forest]]. Tree species include ''[[Acacia nilotica]]'', ''[[Acacia catechu]]'', ''[[Acacia leucophloea]]'', ''[[Tectona hamiltoniana]]'', ''[[Terminalia oliveri]]'', ''[[Xylia dolabriformis]]'' and ''[[Prosopis juliflora]]'', as well as ''[[Dendrocalamus strictus]]'' bamboo clumps.<ref>[http://biostor.org/reference/55673.text Herpetological Expedition to the Minzontaung Wildlife Sanctuary (MWS)]</ref>
The sanctuary protects the [[endangered]] [[Eld's Deer]] and the [[Burmese star tortoise]], a [[Critically Endangered]] species. It is named after Minson Taung, a small isolated massif with a maximum height of 398 m.<ref>[http://turtlesurvival.org/blog/1-blog/160-assessing-reintroduction-sites-for-burmese-star-tortoises Assessing reintroduction sites for Burmese star tortoises]</ref>
